[The appearance of highly pathogenic A/H7N9 variants in poultry indicates that the virus continues to evolve. Although its human to human transmission mechanisms remain largely inefficient, the increasing spread of the virus to various provinces in China and more frequent avian to human transmission events require careful monitoring for the evolutionary changes. - Mod.UBA

